{"analytics_identifier":"PB122","base_path":"/government/organisations/low-pay-commission","content_id":"56026645-0033-45ca-b988-8629a31a9882","description":"The Low Pay Commission is an independent body that advises the government about the National Living Wage and the National Minimum Wage. LPC is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Business and Trade .","details":{"acronym":"LPC","alternative_format_contact_email":"lpc@lowpay.gov.uk","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Low Pay Commission is an independent body that advises the government about the National Living Wage and the National Minimum Wage.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Low Pay Commission\">LPC</abbr> is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/department-for-business-and-trade\">Department for Business and Trade</a>.</p>\n</div>","brand":null,"foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"custom","formatted_title":"Low Pay Commission","image":{"alt_text":"Low Pay Commission","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/59fa00e440f0b62ee8ef89c3/logo_156_X_158.jpg"}},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[{"href":"/government/organisations/low-pay-commission/about/terms-of-reference","title":"Terms of reference"}],"ordered_featured_documents":[{"document_type":"Research","href":"/government/publications/the-national-minimum-wage-in-2026","image":{"alt_text":"Cover of LPC's 2026 uprating report","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ccf6249b2e6e135502d030/s712_2026_uprating_report_cover.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ccf6245cf899414a0bc5d5/s465_2026_uprating_report_cover.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ccf624eafd66b876458b49/2026_uprating_report_cover.png"},"public_updated_at":"2026-04-01T00:05:02.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>This report from the Low Pay Commission looks at the impact of new minimum wage rates in April 2026 and looks ahead at future changes for 2027.</p>\n</div>","title":"The National Minimum Wage in 2026"},{"document_type":"Open consultation","href":"/government/consultations/low-pay-commission-consultation-2026","image":{"alt_text":"LPC logo","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ccf641604bb817c3458b4a/s712_Logo_orange.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ccf6415cf899414a0bc5d8/s465_Logo_orange.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69ccf641837d4b59e502d02b/Logo_orange.png"},"public_updated_at":"2026-04-01T00:05:02.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We are gathering evidence towards our recommendations on minimum wage rates for 2027.</p>\n</div>","title":"Low Pay Commission consultation 2026"},{"document_type":"Research","href":"/government/publications/low-pay-commission-report-2025","image":{"alt_text":"Cover of the LPC's 2025 report","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69a7f755b9bd90e63a252259/s712_2025_report_cover.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69a7f755723a61518b9f140a/s465_2025_report_cover.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69a7f755622103d52c1a9b46/2025_report_cover.jpg"},"public_updated_at":"2026-03-18T08:45:52.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Low Pay Commission’s annual report sets out in full the evidence and analysis which informed recommendations for minimum wage rates from April 2026.</p>\n</div>","title":"Low Pay Commission Report 2025"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/low-pay-commission-regional-visits-2026","image":{"alt_text":"Map of locations the LPC is visiting in 2026","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/69a850495fc94cfb71958f8f/s712_2026_visits.jpg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service