ness-trade","default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/64539946faf4aa0012e132d1/s960_DBT_Plaque-2.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/64539946c33b46000cf5e655/s300_DBT_Plaque-2.jpg"},"logo":{"crest":"dbt","formatted_title":"Department for<br/>Business &amp; Trade"},"organisation_govuk_status":{"status":"live","updated_at":null,"url":null}},"document_type":"organisation","links":{},"locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Department for Business and Trade","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-business-and-trade","withdrawn":false}],"ordered_roles":[{"content_id":"846db7e7-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Chair of the Low Pay Commission is responsible for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>leading Low Pay Commissioners in their deliberations and negotiations, ensuring the Commission provides sound and impartial advice to the Government.</li>\n  <li>presenting the Low Pay Commission’s work to a range of audiences, inside and outside of Government.</li>\n</ul>\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-04-02T13:45:13Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Chair","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"846dd2d3-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>Andrew Goodacre biography</p>\n\n<p>BIRA (British Independent Retailers Association) CEO Andrew Goodacre has devoted his career to strengthening Britain’s high streets and the communities they support. </p>\n\n<p>Since taking over BIRA’s leadership in 2018, Andrew has expanded membership by nearly a third, by ensuring the needs of independent retailers are heard by government decision makers.</p>\n\n<p>Andrew represents BIRA on the Department of Business Retail Sector Council and serves as a member of the British Retail Consortium’s Policy Board and the Welsh Retail Council.</p>\n\n<p>Prior to leading BIRA, Andrew spent many years in the hospitality industry, which helped to reinforce his belief of the importance of local high streets to the fabric of local communities and their contribution to the government’s levelling-up agenda. </p>\n\n<p>Low Pay Commissioner</p>\n\n<p>Commissioners are appointed from an employer background, from an employee background or as independents. Andrew is one of the Commissioners from an employer background.</p>\n\n<p>Andrew was appointed to the Low Pay Commission on 29 January 2024 and his appointment ends on 28 January 2027.</p>\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-03-05T15:38:44Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Low Pay Commissioner","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"846dd322-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Low Pay Commission is a social partnership, made up of Commissioners with experience representing employers, those with experience representing employees and independent Commissioners with expertise in relevant areas. This role is a Commissioner with experience representing employees.</p>\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-04-03T14:13:20Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Low Pay Commissioner","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"846dd373-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Low Pay Commission is a social partnership, made up of Commissioners with experience representing employers, those with experience representing employees and independent Commissioners with expertise in relevant areas. This role is a Commissioner with experience representing employees.</p>\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-04-03T14:11:47Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Low Pay Commissioner","withdrawn":false},{"content_id":"846dd412-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Low Pay Commission is a social pa